1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,640
 Hey, it is so good to be with you today here on Vision Sunday.

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:09,400
 I'm so excited to share with you what we believe God has put on our heart.

3
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:16,800
 And one of the amazing things about being a Christian and a Christian faith is that

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:24,840
 God is not a God who is absent and who is distant, but a God who speaks to his people.

5
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:32,560
 And so the Apostle John, when he received the vision of the end of all things, he recorded

6
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:39,800
 some words from Jesus, "Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the

7
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,800
 churches."

8
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:48,240
 Let me say that again, "Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the

9
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:50,640
 churches."

10
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:55,000
 And so this is what Vision Sunday has always been about.

11
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,740
 It's about us receiving what God is speaking to his church in this season.

12
00:01:00,740 --> 00:01:07,240
 It's about us applying and living out this word with faith, with courage that he is giving

13
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:09,060
 us.

14
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:15,000
 And so today we're going to share what we believe the Holy Spirit has been speaking

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,580
 to us as a leadership, what he has for us in this next season.

16
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:29,400
 And my heart for us today is that we can be united by the Holy Spirit in this vision that

17
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,280
 God has given us.

18
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:35,660
 You know, this always is truly the work of the Spirit when this happens.

19
00:01:35,660 --> 00:01:40,760
 And my heart is also that the Holy Spirit will move here among us, that he will inspire

20
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:47,520
 us and that he will ultimately lead us into this vision together, carrying it out, but

21
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:51,720
 also getting to experience exciting things that God will do.

22
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:56,160
 So on that note, I actually would like to pray for us in that way.

23
00:01:56,160 --> 00:02:05,480
 Heavenly Father, I thank you that you are a God who speaks, that you speak to your church.

24
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:08,000
 And Lord, we want to hear what you say.

25
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:17,160
 We want to receive what you are speaking to us through your Holy Spirit.

26
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:30,680
 And I pray today, Holy Spirit, come, unite us around the work that you are doing and

27
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:37,560
 lead us into the ways that you want us to be part of your work.

28
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:43,720
 Help us be a church that is led by you.

29
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:46,720
 I pray this in your name, Jesus.

30
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,720
 Amen.

31
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:58,320
 Now, to get us started today, I want to need to take you back to 2019, to Vision Sunday

32
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,560
 2019.

33
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:04,320
 So on that day, Pastor Andrew, he shared with us a vision, what is known as the River Model

34
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,320
 Vision.

35
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,520
 And so here you see a photo of that.

36
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,120
 Actually, that was me taking the photo on that day.

37
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:18,920
 You see a vast river network covering a large geographical area, which we know is Hong Kong.

38
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:24,980
 And so part of what God spoke to us in that season was that we needed a shift the way

39
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:27,920
 that we think about ourselves.

40
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:34,040
 Instead of thinking about ourselves as a static building in one location, God was inviting

41
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:40,920
 us to think about ourselves as a river that flows across the land.

42
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:45,120
 And so this vision includes a heart for justice.

43
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:49,140
 This vision includes a heart for the lost.

44
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:57,600
 This vision is about seeing God's river of love permeate every district of Hong Kong,

45
00:03:57,600 --> 00:04:05,240
 touching lives, sharing the gospel message of hope and peace, which we so desperately

46
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:07,600
 need.

47
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:12,100
 And so that lies underneath this vision.

48
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:20,560
 And this is also what led us in 2022 to announce to the church that we are planting a church

49
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:27,800
 in order to put what we believe the Holy Spirit was leading us to do into action, to receive

50
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:32,720
 what the Spirit of God was speaking to His church.

51
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:40,400
 And it's been an incredible journey that many of us have been on together.

52
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:45,200
 So when we announced that, I remember being with Ivan in an empty auditorium in front

53
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:50,960
 of a camera, a live stream, because it was still during COVID restrictions.

54
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:55,640
 And it was in a time when there was a kind of a negative and a depressing mood in the

55
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:58,000
 city.

56
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:03,320
 When we felt like everyone was leaving, people were leaving, moving to other countries because

57
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:07,240
 of COVID restrictions and for other reasons.

58
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:11,320
 Companies were shifting their headquarters from Hong Kong to Singapore.

59
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:19,480
 And we sensed that God was calling us to make this prophetic statement, to plant a church

60
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:26,320
 and through that announce and make, declare and make clear that God is not finished with

61
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,320
 Hong Kong.

62
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,960
 He is at work in the city.

63
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:33,520
 He is hard as to draw people to himself, to reveal himself to people who are hurting,

64
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:39,160
 who are lost, who need change, transformation in their lives.

65
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,760
 And so we stepped forward in faith.

66
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:47,860
 And it was scary at times because it doesn't exist.

67
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:50,040
 But God is so faithful.

68
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:54,120
 And so we give God praise for all that He's done.

69
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,280
 In 2023, we had our soft launch.

70
00:05:56,280 --> 00:06:03,840
 In January 2023, October, we had our first Cantonese and English service in this building.

71
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:07,200
 God is so good.

72
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,680
 It's amazing.

73
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:19,920
 And I know Ivan and I, we got like special front row seats to our amazing God that we

74
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:22,040
 serve.

75
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:32,080
 Now one of the things that is beautiful about that is that God speaks to us as one church.

76
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:35,620
 We are one church in Wanchai, in Yuen Long.

77
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:37,880
 Our northern metropolis.

78
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:46,120
 And He gives us this one broad vision for us as a church family.

79
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:53,000
 But then He invites us in these different occasions to work out what this vision looks

80
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,080
 like.

81
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,480
 And it will express itself in different ways.

82
00:06:57,480 --> 00:07:05,600
 And to celebrate this oneness and this unity that we have, I'm going to invite Pastor Andrew

83
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:12,320
 to share with the video this broad vision that we sense God is speaking to us in this

84
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,320
 season.

85
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:16,520
 And then afterwards, Pastor Ivan and I, we're going to come up and we're going to share

86
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:22,000
 with you how we are discerning that we are led by the Spirit to implement this vision

87
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,080
 here in Yuen Long.

88
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:25,440
 So let's watch the video from Pastor Andrew.

89
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,960
 Well, hey, everyone in Yuen Long.

90
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:34,040
 It is such a privilege to be with you here at Vision Sunday 2026, albeit via this video

91
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,560
 and not actually in person with you.

92
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:38,500
 I'm probably preaching live right now in Wanchai.

93
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:42,520
 But it's great to be able to be with you and share some thoughts and feelings that we have

94
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:48,920
 as a leadership around the vision for the Vine, both here in 2026, but also in the years

95
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,920
 ahead.

96
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:55,120
 Now, you might remember that back in 2025, Pastor Tim told you that the church was in

97
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,840
 a season that we called uncharted.

98
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:02,720
 That we were in this idea that we were like a sailing ship that had moved out from safe

99
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:09,120
 harbor and was going out to explore uncharted territory, uncharted waters.

100
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:12,880
 And we said last year that that was going to be a season of discovery, a season of really

101
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:17,920
 having to trust in the leading of the Holy Spirit, a season of not necessarily knowing

102
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:24,320
 exactly where we're going to end up, but listening and discerning and being led by him as our

103
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,320
 guide.

104
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:30,720
 Now, as we're entering into 2026, we're sensing that that season continues, that he's still

105
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:35,320
 at work in us saying, "This is uncharted and I'm still moving upon you.

106
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:40,080
 And you're not going to have all of the answers, but just trust me as you move forward."

107
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:44,600
 Now as a leadership last year, we were praying, "Okay, God, we know that we're in that season,

108
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:48,560
 but we're also wanting as a church to make sure that we're fit for purpose, that we're

109
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:53,480
 structured in a way that we're catching everything that you want us to do as you move us into

110
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,840
 this uncharted waters time."

111
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:59,840
 And so as we began to pray that, we actually were reminded of the original picture that

112
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:03,680
 God gave us in this uncharted season last year.

113
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:08,760
 You might remember it was a picture of a sailing ship and that sailing ship being out there

114
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,680
 on those waters.

115
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:16,120
 And as God reminded us again of that sailing ship, he said something very specific to us.

116
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:20,040
 He said, "Look, my wind is blowing against you.

117
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:25,200
 My word, my spirit, it's at work blowing the vine forward.

118
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:29,280
 Your responsibility is not the wind, but you do have a responsibility.

119
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:34,040
 Your responsibility is to put the sails up that can catch the wind to move the church

120
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,040
 forward."

121
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:42,040
 In other words, we don't direct the wind, but we can adjust our sails.

122
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:46,560
 We can be a church that's listening and discerning, knowing what the spirit is doing and doing

123
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:51,120
 our best to put up the sails to catch that wind that is blowing against us.

124
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:55,440
 And we felt quite strongly that if we don't do this, we're really going to be a little

125
00:09:55,440 --> 00:10:00,040
 bit like what Paul describes in Ephesians 4, which is where we get the vision of our

126
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,240
 church growing big people from.

127
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:06,360
 In Ephesians 4, he says these words, "If you are not preparing people for the works of

128
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:10,920
 service and building up each other in unity and maturity in the wholeness of the wholeness

129
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:18,880
 of Christ, then you will be like a ship being blown around on every wave of teaching."

130
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,520
 And that's not what we want here at the Vine.

131
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:26,000
 We don't want to be a church that is getting pushed around here and there, kind of almost

132
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:31,640
 dependent on the currents of the water rather than the wind of the spirit that's blowing

133
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:32,960
 against us.

134
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:37,680
 So as we prayed into this as a leadership, we worked out that there were four sails that

135
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:42,760
 we need to put up and adjust in order to catch the wind that is blowing by the spirit on

136
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:43,760
 the Vine.

137
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:48,300
 And so here at Vision Sunday 2026, we want to tell you about these four sails.

138
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:51,820
 This is not the total picture of everything that is happening.

139
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:55,000
 This is not the destination that the Lord has taken us to.

140
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,240
 That's still uncharted.

141
00:10:56,240 --> 00:11:00,080
 But these are the sails that we're going to put up to make sure we're capitalizing on

142
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:03,120
 the wind of His spirit that is blowing at this time.

143
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:06,840
 So let me explain to you what the first sail is, the one that we're going to put up and

144
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,840
 adjust.

145
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:10,440
 It is the presence of the Holy Spirit.

146
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:14,440
 Now this might not be a surprise to you, but this has always been a fundamental focus for

147
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,920
 the Vine since our very inception some 30 years ago.

148
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:22,160
 We've always been a church that's leaned into the reality of the Holy Spirit.

149
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:27,520
 But we feel in this new season that the Lord is saying to us even more that we need to

150
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:33,040
 focus on the priority of the Holy Spirit, focus on His presence amongst us, and focus

151
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:37,640
 on the ministry of the Spirit, what He wants to do, whether that's in our gatherings, whether

152
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:42,520
 that's in our small groups, whether that's across the breadth of all of our ministries.

153
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:46,800
 So one of the things that we're going to be focusing on in the year ahead is really making

154
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:51,960
 intentional room, intentional space within our gatherings and our small group communities

155
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:55,920
 and all of our ministries to allow the Holy Spirit to do what the Holy Spirit wants to

156
00:11:55,920 --> 00:12:01,280
 do, to create that intentional room for Him to come and minister to us, to prioritize

157
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:05,460
 His presence and to allow the Holy Spirit to come and speak.

158
00:12:05,460 --> 00:12:08,600
 That's the way that we grow, it's the way that we change, and that's the way that He's

159
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:12,560
 going to move us into the church that He longs for us to be.

160
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:17,000
 Just a little while ago we were having a worship and prayer night here in Wan Chai, and as

161
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:21,120
 I was just really allowing the Holy Spirit to speak to me, I saw a picture.

162
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:25,760
 And it was a picture of a coffee machine, like the coffee machine that you guys have

163
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,880
 right there in the lounge in Yuen Long.

164
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:32,320
 And the coffee machine was dripping, just little drips of coffee.

165
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:35,760
 And as I was looking at this, I asked the Lord, "What is going on here?

166
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:38,200
 It seems like the coffee machine is broken."

167
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:42,680
 And He said, "Look, the coffee machine represents my spirit and the way in which my spirit is

168
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,620
 moving on the vine.

169
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:50,360
 Right now, it's like I'm just dripping little bits of my spirit upon you as a church.

170
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:53,960
 My heart is that I want the coffee, if you will, to flow.

171
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:58,400
 I want my spirit to flow, but right now it's just a little bit, it's dripping."

172
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:02,240
 And I said to the Spirit as I was getting this, I said, "Why only dripping?

173
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:04,280
 Why not flowing fully?"

174
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:09,120
 And He said, "Well, there's no cup underneath to catch the pour."

175
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:12,120
 And I realized when I saw the picture of the coffee machine that there wasn't actually

176
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,880
 a cup underneath it.

177
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:16,620
 And so I said to God, "Well, what is the cup?"

178
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:20,400
 And God said this, and I found it very personally challenging, and I think it's something challenging

179
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,900
 for us as a church community.

180
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:28,020
 He said, "The cup is trust, that in order for me to flow my spirit and the passion that

181
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:32,440
 I have for it to flow, there's going to have to be an increased level of trust.

182
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:38,600
 Trust in me, trust in the Spirit by both the leadership across both the Vinewanchai and

183
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:44,760
 Yuen Long, as well as our elderships in both locations, but also individually, us, you

184
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:49,920
 and I, we're going to have to be open to trust the work of the Spirit more and more in our

185
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:50,920
 lives.

186
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:54,080
 And as we build trust, the Spirit is going to flow."

187
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:59,280
 So that's the first cell, presence of the Holy Spirit, ministry in the Holy Spirit,

188
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:03,160
 and prioritizing that presence in our lives.

189
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,160
 Here's the second cell.

190
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,160
 It is radical discipleship.

191
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:11,520
 And if you think about it for a moment, those two things flow from each other.

192
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:16,160
 When the work of the Spirit is more and more at work amongst us, when we're being changed

193
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:21,960
 and transformed, convicted of our sin, receiving inner healing through the work of the Spirit,

194
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:25,480
 then the most natural thing is that we will grow in discipleship.

195
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:30,700
 We will, like our vision says in Ephesians 4, become more and more like Christ Jesus.

196
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:36,040
 And so our second cell that we're going to put up and adjust is radical discipleship.

197
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:41,020
 And it's going to be a strong call to us as a church community to really position ourselves

198
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:44,660
 to live for Jesus in our city in this time.

199
00:14:44,660 --> 00:14:49,160
 We know that the Lord loves Hong Kong so much, and we know that Hong Kong is in a pivotal

200
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,240
 time of its history.

201
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:55,120
 And really the challenge the Spirit is bringing to us is, is the Vine going to be a church

202
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:57,960
 of faith, hope and love in the years ahead?

203
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:04,000
 Or are we going to shrink back into our own self-preservation and our own self-concerns?

204
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,540
 Are we willing to stand up and stand out?

205
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:09,720
 Or are we going to shrink back and fade out?

206
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:14,200
 And this call to radical discipleship is a call to ensure that we as a church community,

207
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:20,840
 both individually and corporately, can continue to be a church of boldness, a church of courage,

208
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:25,760
 and a church of Jesus, revealing Jesus to the city around us.

209
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:30,840
 As we prayed about this last year as a leadership, we actually heard really a sense in the Lord

210
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:35,480
 that there were some things that He wanted us to do in this area of discipleship.

211
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:39,560
 And we've kind of put a document together that we're calling the guiding principles.

212
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:43,560
 These are principles that we sense that the Spirit is saying to us that will shape our

213
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:47,940
 discipleship not just in 2026, but in the years to come.

214
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:51,440
 Now there are five elements to this guiding principle.

215
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:55,400
 And you're going to be hearing a lot more about this in the months ahead as we teach

216
00:15:55,400 --> 00:16:00,960
 more directly on this in our services across the breadth of both Wonchai and Yuen Long.

217
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:04,200
 But let me introduce you, first of all, to these five things.

218
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,560
 They are as follows.

219
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:09,440
 Number one, surrendered to Scripture.

220
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:13,800
 This idea that the Bible needs to shape everything we do in life.

221
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,920
 Number two, priority of presence.

222
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:20,520
 Again, leaning into the reality of the Holy Spirit and His work in our lives.

223
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:23,100
 Number three, centered on Jesus.

224
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:28,500
 This focus that we have of making Jesus the priority in everything we do.

225
